      it's one of those songs where it has a music video also, to go along with the song. released as a video, and also as just the song so you can listen to it on-the-go if you prefer

      i have a bucket to catch the inspiration but sometimes the bucket itself inspires me

12.31.20  11:09 pm   i had a dream a few nights ago that my dad told me to make a loaf of bread shaped like a dog. do you think that this is something that is possible in real life?

      yes

      i didn't even notice

12.31.20  9:22 pm   What potions do you take in the morning?

      water

12.31.20  8:23 pm   do you ever cringe when you realised you accidentally typed a capital letter

      no

12.31.20  7:51 pm   what will you do for the new year

      make as many videos and songs as i can

12.31.20  6:52 pm   What do you think about legos?

      could use more purple and pink legos

12.31.20  6:48 pm   How do I stop being anxious?

      sing songs of joy

12.31.20  6:16 pm   would you ever write a song longer than 5 minutes

      anything of that length will probably be much more than a song. it may include music or even songs. but it would not be just 1 song, and it would not be only songs

12.31.20  6:15 pm   How are you so funny

      that could be due to the extreme levels of normalcy i have cultivated

12.31.20  5:26 pm   How did you discover you were so creative?

      i once played e2-e6, as an opening move in a chess game

12.31.20  5:17 pm   While making your new video, have you ever thought of trying to make vlogs or some small videos while we are waiting? I'm not telling you do it I'm asking if you ever thought about it.

      if you're waiting, and i'm making a small video, then ........... who's making the normal sized video?

12.31.20  4:18 pm   are you having a happy new year?

      the year i'm currently in is actually very old

12.31.20  3:49 pm   How would you describe "art" by itself?

      i'd have to just try to explain the art. but first i would search for ways to actually show it to the other person, because that is much better than describing it

12.31.20  3:34 pm   What was the song that you wrote on that airplane

      i wrote many things but none of them have been finished. i was working on one thing that might have sounded similar to Mount st Helens but then a couple days later i had the idea for Mount st Helens and did that instead of the other one. the other one would have been a good second choice, but it's been mostly excluded since then due to too much similarity to Mount St Helens. but it is a good one and i would like to do it, as soon as enough time passes that people won't be too mad at me for it sounding too similar to Mount st Helens

12.31.20  2:30 pm   does the end of the year make you feel anything special?

      it's not supposed to, but, it is another ugly reminder of how long i've been stuck in this terrifying patch of quicksand

12.31.20  2:10 pm   hey make more songs!

      i almost didn't even think of that

      be normal

      i may have left myself in a field a few times

      are you really incapable of ....... noticing all of the capital letters i use?

      let me perform some calculations

p.s. i know almost no music theory just some chords and major scale

      what other instruments do you like

      trying to think about how it originally felt when i first wrote it

12.31.20  11:00 am   how are you feeling right now?

      like an idiot, but also very smart

12.31.20  10:27 am   flash player is going soon
are you big sad?

      remind me again what it's used for

12.31.20  9:13 am   have you ever seen/listened to something so incredible that you felt both filled with inspiration and also existential hopelessness at the knowledge you will never be able to make something quite as good?

      yes

12.31.20  8:29 am   What are the side effects of trying to do infinity?

      accomplishing nothing

12.31.20  7:41 am   What do you think of personality-clasification systems?

      the confusing part is, every personality is good

12.31.20  6:37 am   are keyboards cool?

      i was going to say no but now that i think about it yes

12.31.20  5:25 am   are you doing anything for new years?

      i'm going to be making ~content~ for the entire year and also other years. as many times as possible

12.31.20  4:18 am   Bill, when do you intend on coming back? You are the one thing that gives me serotonin and whatever that other happy chemical was, come here now.

      think of it this way, i don't intend to leave

12.31.20  3:15 am   Long or short videos?

      MEDIUM!

12.31.20  2:02 am   how would you explain making music, like as a concept?

     it's like building a world

      I've been trying to write music but I guess I don't really "get" it.

      no one does. that's one of the reasons music is so ridiculous

12.31.20  1:05 am   Bill, do you actually like surrealism?

     it's one of the basics

     Is it one of your favorite types of art? 

     it's like a good solid foundation to work from

12.31.20  12:45 am   I'm having trouble coming up with a name for an instrumental I just wrote... any ideas?

      find something that is connected to the circumstance when you wrote the song. what else might have been on your mind that day

12.31.20  12:21 am   Why are your songs soo good at helping deal with stress. Thanks btw

      i may have dealt with some of the stress before you did, and i try to put all the lessons i've learned into the music

12.30.20  11:59 pm   Are you planning to release any music sometime soon? No pressure>

      i've always planned to release very much music, on a weekly basis. but those those plans are often sabotaged by some kind of strange and relentless greed

12.30.20  10:38 pm   Can we see the lessons you learned written down in the language of love?

      sure, if i can learn how to stop getting royally in the way of myself

12.30.20  10:09 pm   My favourite thing about your music is that your lyrics are so interpretable. They might seem random to some but I've always felt they are just specific enough to be applied many different scenarios, usually someone who is going on some kind of journey. Personally, I've often noticed transgender themes that seem to be present in your lyrics. In both And The Day Goes On and Outside you talk about changing your name, and When I Get Older has that lyric about changing your face. I've also clocked similar themes of understanding identity and leaving previous lives behind in order to explore things that are considered taboo in songs like Mount St. Helens, We Could Just Get High, I'm Best Friends With My Own Front Door, Movie Star, and It's Gonna Be Alright (I could list specific examples but it would take too long). Just curious what your thoughts are on this interpretation?

      it's pretty good

12.30.20  10:01 pm   how did u build up ur vocabulary with cool chords ??!?!?!?!??!

      listen to a lot of music, play a lot of the music you heard, and also make up your own
